Package gov.tak.api.ui

Class Pane

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.tak.api.ui.Pane
  • public abstract class Pane
extends java.lang.Object
    Opaque representation for a _pane_ added to the UI via IHostUIService.

    Original native representation may be retrieved via MarshalManager per the associated type used to construct with the .

    Each IPane instance may have associated metadata which provide hints to the host application about how the pane should be displayed. All metadata values are optional, and default values will be used if not supplied.

    • Field Detail

      • PREFERRED_WIDTH_RATIO

        public static java.lang.String PREFERRED_WIDTH_RATIO
        Specifies the preferred width of the pane, as a ratio of the main view when no other panes are showing.

        If both PREFERRED_WIDTH_RATIO and PREFERRED_WIDTH_PIXELS are specified, PREFERRED_WIDTH_PIXELS will take precedence.

      • PREFERRED_HEIGHT_RATIO

        public static java.lang.String PREFERRED_HEIGHT_RATIO
        Specifies the preferred height of the pane, as a ratio of the main view when no other panes are showing.

        If both PREFERRED_HEIGHT_RATIO and PREFERRED_HEIGHT_PIXELS are specified, PREFERRED_HEIGHT_PIXELS will take precedence.

      • PREFERRED_WIDTH_PIXELS

        public static java.lang.String PREFERRED_WIDTH_PIXELS
        Specifies the preferred width of the pane, in pixels.

        If both PREFERRED_WIDTH_RATIO and PREFERRED_WIDTH_PIXELS are specified, PREFERRED_WIDTH_PIXELS will take precedence.

      • PREFERRED_HEIGHT_PIXELS

        public static java.lang.String PREFERRED_HEIGHT_PIXELS

        If both PREFERRED_HEIGHT_RATIO and PREFERRED_HEIGHT_PIXELS are specified, PREFERRED_HEIGHT_PIXELS will take precedence.
